fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.vars

Class VariableSink

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.vars.VariableSink

  • public class VariableSink
extends java.lang.Object
    The class VariableSink describes how imported variables are used in a model i.e., either a variable directly imported by an atomic model or a variable imported by a coupled model and then reimported by a submodel; note that in a coupled model, a single imported variable can be reimported by many submodels possibly using different names and types.

    Description

    This class is used to described how imported variables of a coupled model are connected to its submodels.

    Invariant

     invariant       importedVariableName != null
 invariant       importedVariableType != null
 invariant       sinkVariableName != null
 invariant       sinkVariableType != null
 invariant       sinkVariableType.isAssignableFrom(importedVariableType)
 invariant       sinkModelURI != null

    Created on : 2018-06-29

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
